context: The Tucson metro area is served by many local television stations and is the 68th largest designated market area (DMA) in the U.S. with 433,310 homes (0.39% of the total U.S.). It is limited to the three counties of southeastern Arizona (Pima, Santa Cruz, and Cochise) The major television networks serving Tucson are: <a0_0>KVOA 4<a0_0/> (NBC), <a1_0>KGUN 9<a1_0/> (ABC), <a2_0>KMSB-TV 11<a2_0/> (Fox), <a3_0>KOLD-TV 13<a3_0/> (CBS), KTTU 18 (My Network TV) and KWBA 58 (The CW). <a4_0>KUAT-TV 6<a4_0/> is a PBS affiliate run by the University of Arizona (as is sister station KUAS 27).
